						<summary>

						<p>Chōḻa, Rājakēsarivarman, 18th year = c. 10th Century.</p>						

						<p>One Nambaṉ Kēsuvaṉ purchased and gifted some land for lamp to the temple of Teṉkayilāyattu-Mahādēva. He got the land freed from taxes by paying tax capital to the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of the village.</p>						

						<p>(Published in <hi rend="italic">SII</hi>, Vol. XIII, No. 283).</p>						

